25/04/2006
LARISSA, Greece -- An incident involving an Air Force Phantom was reported in the eastern city of Larissa early Tuesday (25 April). Details are sketchy, but according to local media, the two-seater went down near the airport shortly before landing. The two pilots were not injured. 
In other news Tuesday, violent protests marred a daylong visit to Athens by US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice. She met with Greek counterpart Dora Bakoyannis before talks with Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis. Athens is the first stop on Rice's regional tour, which includes meetings in Ankara and Sofia. (ERT, ANA - 25/04/06) 
